<h1>Rules</h1>

<p>
  Rule #1: When something occurs that is not explicitly explained in the rules but where
  there is a precedent based on how we've done things in the past, that precedent will
  serve as a rule.
</p>
<p>
  The scoring in the competition is based on the matches in the English Premier League.    
</p>
<p>
  Points scored in rescheduled matches will be counted for the match day the match was
  originally scheduled for. Example: Match day 5 is played on November 10th. The match
  between Arsenal and Aston Villa is rescheduled for March 5th. The points scored in
  that game will be added to the results in match day 5 when the match is played.
</p>

<h2>Scoring</h2>
<p>
  The teams in the D11 league will play each other twice every season in 38 match days. The team
  that scores the most goals in each match will gain 3 points, the loser will gain 0 points. If
  the game ends in a draw both teams will get 1 point each.
</p>
<p>
  Goals are awarded based on the number of player points the team accumulates in each match.
</p>

