<p>
  The team with the most points after 38 match days wins the league. If two or more
  teams have the same number of points, the team who's scored the most goals wins.
  If two or more teams still can't be separated, the team who's conceded the most goals wins.
  If a winner still can't be found the league will be decided by a penalty shootout at Nabben stadium.
</p>
<p>
  The fixture list will be made after the draft and published on this website.
</p>
<p>
  Match stats and ratings will be taken from www.whoscored.com. If Whoscored for some reason
  fail to produce stats or ratings then stats will be taken from www.premierleague.com and ratings
  will be taken from www.skysports.com. The stats and ratings will be updated soon after the matches
  are finished but as Whoscored has a habit of updating the ratings after a while the ratings will
  be finalized at approximately 18:00 the day after the match was played.
</p>
<p>
  The Man of the Match (MoM) for each team in a Premier League match will be
  the player with the highest rating on www.whoscored.com. If two players on the same team share
  the highest rating then both of them will be shared MoM. If three or more players on the same team
  share the highest rating then no MoM will be chosen for that team.
</p>

